President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These appointments include Leonard Andrew Forsman as a member and vice chair of the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation, Linda Behnken as the United States Commissioner for the International Pacific Halibut Commission, Beth White as a member of the National Capital Planning Commission, Donna Darm as the United States Commissioner for the Pacific Salmon Commission, Charles O. Swanton as the United States Commissioner for the Pacific Salmon Commission, Earl A. Powell III as a member of the Commission of Fine Arts, and Elizabeth K. Meyer as a member of the Commission of Fine Arts. Additionally, Charles D. Brower and Gregory Siekaniec have been appointed as United States Commissioners for the U.S.-Russia Polar Bear Commission. President Obama has expressed his gratitude for the service of these individuals and looks forward to working with them.